  "texts": [
    "Each trait score can be modeled as it fits to the trait definition.",
    "For example, argumentative or narrative essays do not possess a prompt adherence trait, which means that prompts designed for argumentative or narrative essay types will not be scored based on the prompt adherence trait quality.",
    "Enhancing traits with trait-specific features: He et al. (2022) proposed a Hierarchical Multi-task Trait Scorer (HMTS) for the Chinese AES task.",
    "The architecture consists of two layers: the common layer and the private layer.",
    "The common layer is dedicated to learning sentence and paragraph representations."
  ],
